    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 233.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In connection with the Department’s note
                    of the 22d instant, I have the honor to apprise you of the receipt of a letter
                    from the Acting Secretary of the Treasury, wherein, it appears, with reference
                    to the trial of the schooner <hi rend="italic">Marvin</hi>, that Capt. C. L.
                    Hooper, commanding the revenue steamer <hi rend="italic">Rush</hi>, which vessel
                    seized the <hi rend="italic">Marvin</hi>, and Lieut. F. S. Van Boskerck, jr.,
                    who boarded and examined that vessel, have been instructed by telegraph to
                    proceed immediately to Victoria for the purpose of giving testimony in that
                    case.</p>
                <p>The officers of the <hi rend="italic">Corwin</hi>, which vessel seized the <hi
                        rend="italic">Shelby</hi>, were ordered several days ago to proceed to
                    Victoria.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
